<P>
FRAISE IS THIRD IN THE MCKNIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cobblestone Road scored a major upset in the $150,000 W.L. McKnight Handicap 
and longshot Fabulous Frolic won the $100,000 Tropical Park Derby for 
3-year-olds as Calder Race Course closed its 50-day winter meeting on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Cobblestone Road, a 29-1 shot, led for the entire 1 1/2 miles on the grass, 
holding off Daarik by 1 1/4 lengths.Fraise, the 1-2 favorite, was third, 1 3/4 
lengths behind Daarik. 
</P>
<P>
 Going into the Grade II race, Fraise, ridden by Chris McCarron, had earned 
$2,265,605 in 25 starts, while Cobblestone Road had earned $160,994 in 38 
races. 
</P>
<P>
 Cobblestone Road, ridden by Jose Ferrer, was timed in 2:27 4/5 and paid 
$61.20, $22.80 and $6.60. Daarik paid $5.80 and $2.40 and Fraise paid $2.20. 
</P>
<P>
 Fabulous Frolic won by 1 1/2 lengths over Wake Up Alarm, the 2-1 favorite. 
</P>
<P>
 Fabulous Frolic ran 1 1/8 miles on the grass in 1:46 4/5 and paid $33, $10.60 
and $7.60. Wake Up Alarm returned $4.40 and $3.80 and Gator Back paid $5.60. 
</P>
<P>
 Poolesta came from behind under Robbie Davis to beat Raise Heck by a nose in 
the $100,000 Interborough Breeders' Cup at Aqueduct. 
</P>
