<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jeff Meyers 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 WEATHER WATCH: Words seldom used by residents of Ventura County unless talking 
to relatives in the Midwest: frostbite , wind-chill factor , slush , 
hypothermia. . . . Even our coldest temperatures this month seem balmy compared 
with those in other parts of the country. . . . Fargo, N. D., for example, 
averages a high of 4 degrees and a low of minus 4, with the wind-chill factor 
often hitting 70 below zero. . . . The nation's hot spot in January? Honolulu, 
with an average low of only 66. 
</P>
<P>
 NEW LIFE: Robert V. Biroschak was 50 when he gave up his law practice in 1989 
to study for the Roman Catholic priesthood (Voices, B11). . . . Now associate 
pastor at Our Lady of the Assumption in Ventura, Father Bob was never married 
and didn't really surprise friends by becoming a priest. . . . "Religion was 
always important to me, but I wasn't a church mouse," he said. "At 8 or 9, I 
knew I wanted to be a priest, but it took me a long time to say yes." He has no 
ambitions other than "to be the best priest I can be." 
</P>
<P>
 LOW BRIDGES: A project to build a new bridge over Santa Paula Freeway will 
cost $6.5 million more than expected (B1). . . . But the bridges of Ventura 
County -- hey, good title for a book -- didn't always cost megabucks. The 
county's first cement span, the Harmon Barranca Bridge on Telephone Road in 
Ventura, was built in 1896 for $9,500. . . . In 1912, the Ventura River Bridge 
cost $49,626. . . . The longest bridge in county history, a 300-foot span 
crossing Sespe Creek in Fillmore, was destroyed by high water in 1914. 
</P>
<P>
 ROAD REPAIRS: Buried deep beneath the pavement, a worn-out traffic signal 
detector has been causing dangerous conditions at the intersection of Agoura 
Road and Westlake Boulevard, but the city of Thousand Oaks plans to correct the 
problem later this month (Street Smart, B1). . . . After scores of complaints 
by motorists, Oxnard restriped Rose Avenue to allow safer access into the 
Shopping at the Rose parking lot. Cold Month 
</P>
<P>
 Average low temperatures Ojai: 37 Moorpark: 41 Fillmore: 41 Santa Paula: 41 
Camarillo: 42 Thousand Oaks: 43 Simi Valley: 44 Oxnard: 44 Ventura: 44 Port 
Hueneme: 46 
</P>
