<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: MEDIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scripps Sells English-Language San Juan Star: The San Juan Star, Puerto Rico's 
only English-language daily newspaper, has been sold to a group of U.S. and 
Puerto Rican investors, the newspaper reported Sunday. Scripps Howard, the 
Cincinnati-based publishing unit of E.W. Scripps, did not reveal the purchase 
price, the paper said.But the Star estimated it as between $10 million and $14 
million, and said the latter figure was he book value of the paper. The 
purchaser is Santa Rita Acquisitions Inc., a Delaware corporation formed by a 
group of U.S. and Puerto Rican investors. The newspaper, which has a 
circulation of about 40,000, said he sale followed a difficult year, with 
revenues totaling $16.5 million and a net loss projected at nearly $500,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
