<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; COUPLE HOSPITALIZED AFTER CAR ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Nevada couple remained hospitalized Sunday after the car they were traveling 
in tumbled off a steep embankment on Grimes Canyon Road near Moorpark late 
Saturday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The car that Melissa Tibbetts, 18, and Daniel Thorton, 19, were in went off 
the road near Shekell Road about 9:20 p.m., according to Ventura County 
Sheriff's Sgt. Terry Hughes.Officials believe that the car dropped 200 to 300 
feet below the roadway. 
</P>
<P>
 Hughes said Ventura County firefighters had to rescue Tibbetts, who suffered 
several broken bones, after she became trapped inside the car. Thorton, who 
suffered minor internal injuries, managed to free himself and flag down a 
passing motorist. 
</P>
<P>
 They were taken to Los Robles Regional Medical Center in Thousand Oaks, where 
Tibbetts was listed in fair condition and Thorton was listed in stable 
condition as of Sunday afternoon, according to a nursing supervisor. 
</P>
<P>
 Hughes said the sheriff's major crimes unit and the California Highway Patrol 
were investigating the accident. He declined to give more details. A CHP 
spokeswoman also declined comment on the case. J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
