<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEMPERATURES SOAR TO RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Summery temperatures broke a 101-year-old record Sunday as the weather brought 
thousands of Southland residents to the beaches, and tantalized visiting 
Wisconsin football fans as they boarded planes for home. 
</P>
<P>
 A high-pressure system pushed the temperature to 84 degrees at 2 p.m. at the 
Civic Center. That was one degree higher than the Jan. 2 record set in 1893, 
according to the National Weather Service. 
</P>
<P>
 In Glendale, it hit 87 degrees, the warmest in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
