<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 MEN CHARGED WITH CARRYING MOLOTOV COCKTAILS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three men were arrested during a traffic stop early Sunday after Los Angeles 
County sheriff's deputies found Molotov cocktails, a flare gun and containers 
of gasoline in their car, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputies from the Lennox station had stopped the vehicle for speeding near 
113th Street and Normandie Avenue about 3:30 a.m., and noticed a heavy odor of 
gasoline coming from inside their vehicle, Deputy Diane Hecht said. 
</P>
<P>
 The deputies found four of the incendiary Molotov cocktails -- bottles filled 
with fuel and plugged with a wick that is ignited and hurled. They also found a 
flare gun, ski masks, gloves and several containers of gas. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, Isaac Nash, 21, of Los Angeles, and passengers Jonathan Turner, 
21, of Indio, and William Morrell, 21, of Long Beach, were arrested on 
suspicion of possession of a destructive device, Hecht said. 
</P>
<P>
 They were jailed in lieu of $100,000 bail each, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 The three men refused to say why they had the explosives or what they planned 
to do with them, Hecht said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
