<P>
ELECTRICAL PANEL BLAMED IN RESEDA FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fire that damaged a Reseda cycle shop Saturday night, causing $220,000 in 
damages, was caused by an electrical problem inside the shop, according to the 
Los Angeles Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Fifty-five firefighters battled the blaze at Vick's Custom Cycle Shop at 17644 
Sherman Way for 40 minutes to prevent it from spreading to an adjoining shop, 
My Gym. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire was confined to the attic and mezzanine area of the cycle shop, Fire 
Department spokesman Brian Humphrey said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire investigators determined that the blaze started in an electrical panel. 
There was $120,000 in damage to the structure and $100,000 in damage to the 
contents of the building. 
</P>
