<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VIRGINIA FANS COME OUT 35 STRONG TO WELCOME TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Only 35 fans turned out Sunday night to greet the West Virginia football team 
after its 41-7 loss to Florida in the Sugar Bowl the previous day. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was very surprised we even had any fans out here," sophomore tackle Vann 
Washington said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have the greatest fans in the country," offensive line coach Dave 
McMichael said. "They're loyal, good people. It's a shame we couldn't have 
played better. We shot ourselves in the foot." 
</P>
<P>
 Said Edie Harper of Morgantown: "People supported them all through the year, 
but now where are they when they lose? Where are the true Mountaineer fans?" 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA010394-0151 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 000757 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
