<TEXT>
<P>
 English Channel Tunnel Fare Set: Motorists traveling through the tunnel 
between England and France may need something more than a sense of adventure. A 
fat wallet, for instance.The Sunday Times reported that the round-trip fare for 
taking a car through the tunnel will be about $240. From May to June and 
October to December a standard round-trip ticket will sell for about $240 per 
car, rising to $330 to $360 during the busiest tourist season, the newspaper 
said. The fares for the 31-mile Channel tunnel, nicknamed the Chunnel, would be 
slightly more expensive than those for much slower ferries, but low enough to 
plunge ferry operators into a fare price war, the newspaper reported. Passenger 
service will begin in May. 
</P>
